ior to being deported by the Nazis into concentration camps. His father survived the war but died when the author was a teenager, leaving him only with the knowledge that he had buried coins somewhere in Poland, and no information about his family. During his quest, Biederman uncovers many interesting and disturbing facts about his father and mother and their families, such as the fact that his father was the third person on Oskar Schindler's list and had a chance meeting with Adolph Hitler, and that his mother was selected as a cook for the infamous Dr. Josef Mengele. The book details the author's quest to unearth his family's past and hist father's treasure and continues with his parent's amazing post-war years in Europe and their eventual arrival in North America.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Feb 2020) 4a2nd generation Holocaust memoirs. 4aAuschwitz-Birkenau. 4aAuschwitz. 4aGenealogy. 4aHolocaust memoirs. 4aHolocaust survivors. 4aHolocaust. 4aJosef Mengele. 4aPoland. 4aPoles. 4aSchindler's List. 4aSecond World War. 4aTreasure Hunt. 4aWWII. 4aWarsaw. 4aWorld War II. 4aWorld War Tow:World War 2:WW2. 4aantisemitism. 4asecond generation Holocaust survivor. 4asurvival memory. 4asurvival. 4atreasure hunting. 4atreatment of Jews by Poles. 7aHISTORY / Holocaust.2bisacsh1 aBiederman, Randi08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertASP eBook Package 2019z978311068819108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019 Englishz978311061076508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2019z9783110664232oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019 Englishz978311061017808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2019z9783110606195oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://d